node.text:
As I continue to show my support for small businesses just like @QuickBooks does every day, I’m excited to highlight one of my all-time favorites – Cal Skate.
Some of my best childhood memories were made there and I’m so happy they’re still providing fun for those in Chico. They need all the support they can get after an extremely challenging last year and I couldn’t think of a better place to show some extra love to.
Next time you’re nearby, stop in and let them know I sent you 💪🏻💪🏻 #BackSmallBiz #sponsored #buttestrong #chico #

node.text: Been on the phone with Jay Don Blake, Mark McCumber, Bruce Lietzke, Steve Elkington, and other greats from the 90s doing some research on how to get in jabba’s (@philmickelson) dome. These dudes used to beat up on him every week before the Tim Herron’s of the world did. Valuable intel for @brysondechambeau and I, not that we will need much help. #thematch #calfgamestrong #bananasliceguy #jabba #imoffended #

node.text:
This is a highlight video of the round 2 calls we made for our grants to small businesses in Butte County through our Small Business Covid 19 Relief Fund with our partners at @northvalleycf 

We are SO THANKFUL to @jeopardy and the numerous other donors for helping make this possible, and most of all...

We are SO PROUD to highlight these amazing businesses ❤️ who have been so deeply affected by the pandemic and the lockdown rules. 

May we all continue to spread love and hope to our friends and neighbors, and use kindness and empathy as our road to connection. 

Big thanks to @mrs.bensonvalavanis at @NVCF and her incredible team there. 🙏🏻❤️
#spreadlove❤️

@northvalleycf #

node.text:
A staple for decades in our community, next up is 
Kona’s! 💪🏼 Kona’s has been in existence since 1993. The Main Street location in downtown Chico is a restaurant and bakery, selling bread to more than 30 local businesses. Owner Chris Yarbrough says sales are down 50% but no employees have been laid off. Not on our watch 💪🏼 #2093 #smallbusinessfund #spreadlove❤ @northvalleycf

node.text: The Bookstore, owned by Josh Seth Mills, occupies a historic brick building on Main Street in downtown Chico and has been in operation nearly 45 years. The large space is charmingly crammed with used books and you can browse for hours, but a lack of foot traffic has led to a sharp drop in business. #smallbusinessfund #spreadlove❤ @northvalleycf

node.text:
Next up is a great coffee spot! 
Cal Java’s location on The Esplanade in Chico, owned by Nicole McHenry, has been greatly affected by the pandemic. The coffee shop is right next to Enloe Medical Center. Doctors, nurses and families visiting hospital patients would frequent the shop for breakfast, lunch or coffee breaks -- and then indoor dining was forbidden. Now they’re in the fund!!! 💪🏼💪🏼 #smallbusinessfund  #spreadlove❤️ @northvalleycf

node.text: If you lived in Chico in the last 30 years, you know about Aca Taco!!🔥🔥 Aca Taco is a family-owned business that opened their first location in 1994 on Nord Avenue to cater to college neighborhoods. Owner Martha Herrera Hernandez opened a second location in 1996 in downtown Chico. #smallbusinessfund #spreadlove❤  @northvalleycf

node.text: Next business up in the small business fund is the Naked Lounge, owned by Michael Lee, it is a coffee shop in the heart of downtown Chico. Naked Lounge likes to say it “embraces the unconventional, the off-center, the unique, the self-starters, and the idea-generators.” So excited to be able to help out this special place which has been a staple in our city for decades. #smallbusinessfund #spreadlove❤️ @northvalleycf

node.text:
Helen’s Donut Nook
 
As I continue to show my support for small businesses just like @QuickBooks does every day, I wanted to recognize one of my favorite small businesses in Chico - Helen’s Donut Nook.
 
They have served donuts in downtown Chico for over 50 years and have some of the hardest working owners I know. They survived the pandemic last year and I’m so proud to give them the recognition they deserve. They are true champions of our community.
 
Let me know your small business stories and I can’t wait to share more of mine this week #BackSmallBiz #sponsored #chicostrong💪 #gratitude #

node.text:
As I continue to show my support for small businesses just like @QuickBooks does every day, I’m excited to highlight one of my all-time favorites – Cal Skate.
Some of my best childhood memories were made there and I’m so happy they’re still providing fun for those in Chico. They need all the support they can get after an extremely challenging last year and I couldn’t think of a better place to show some extra love to.
Next time you’re nearby, stop in and let them know I sent you 💪🏻💪🏻 #BackSmallBiz #sponsored #buttestrong #chico #

node.text: Been on the phone with Jay Don Blake, Mark McCumber, Bruce Lietzke, Steve Elkington, and other greats from the 90s doing some research on how to get in jabba’s (@philmickelson) dome. These dudes used to beat up on him every week before the Tim Herron’s of the world did. Valuable intel for @brysondechambeau and I, not that we will need much help. #thematch #calfgamestrong #bananasliceguy #jabba #imoffended #

node.text:
This is a highlight video of the round 2 calls we made for our grants to small businesses in Butte County through our Small Business Covid 19 Relief Fund with our partners at @northvalleycf 

We are SO THANKFUL to @jeopardy and the numerous other donors for helping make this possible, and most of all...

We are SO PROUD to highlight these amazing businesses ❤️ who have been so deeply affected by the pandemic and the lockdown rules. 

May we all continue to spread love and hope to our friends and neighbors, and use kindness and empathy as our road to connection. 

Big thanks to @mrs.bensonvalavanis at @NVCF and her incredible team there. 🙏🏻❤️
#spreadlove❤️
